      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2) is operated under a documented software quality assurance plan including version control, regression testing, and formal release validation. SQA documentation reviewed and confirmed compliant with ASME V&V 40 Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification performed via comparison against analytical solutions for Poiseuille flow and lid-driven cavity benchmarks. Observed order of accuracy consistent with second-order spatial discretization scheme. Results archived in verification report MCV-VER-2024-01."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation-based grid convergence index (GCI) computed across three systematically refined meshes (3.2 M, 8.7 M, and 22.4 M cells). GCI for shear stress scalar (hemolysis driver) below 4% on fine mesh. Temporal discretization verified via time-step halving study with < 1% change in RH index."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions documented in FDA pump benchmark protocol. Fluid temperature (37°C), blood analog viscosity (3.5 cP), hematocrit (35%), and inlet/outlet boundary conditions replicated in CFD setup. Deviations from nominal conditions quantified and bounded within ±5% for all parameters."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against published FDA pump experimental data across 5 operating points. Mean absolute error of 12.3% with no systematic bias. Comparison conducted using standardized metrics per ASME V&V 20."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) derived from volume-integrated scalar shear stress using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. This QoI directly maps to the clinical endpoint (plasma-free hemoglobin elevation) and is the accepted regulatory metric for CPB pump hemolysis assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is geometrically and operationally analogous to the CPB pump COU. Operating conditions (flow rates 2.5–7 L/min, speeds 2500–4500 RPM) span the intended COU envelope. Validation domain overlap assessed as high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via residual drop to 10^-6 for continuity and momentum equations. Mass imbalance across inlet/outlet confirmed below 0.01%. Solver floating-point precision set to double throughout. No divergence events observed across 47 simulation runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not evaluated in this assessment cycle.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team determined that use error is not a relevant consideration for this purely computational workflow, as the CFD model is executed by trained simulation engineers under a controlled analysis protocol with no end-user interaction at the point of clinical use. Accordingly, no structured use-error assessment was conducted and no required or achieved gradation levels were assigned. The factor is carried as not-assessed rather than not-applicable because a formal applicability determination per Table 5-1 was not completed prior to package submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published literature demonstrating superior performance for rotating confined flows with adverse pressure gradients. Hemolysis sub-model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) validated against in-vitro data. Sensitivity analysis across three turbulence model variants (k-ε realizable, RSM, SST k-ω) confirms RH predictions within 8% across models."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions, material constants) sourced from peer-reviewed literature and FDA benchmark documentation. Input uncertainty ranges defined for 8 parameters; one-at-a-time sensitivity study performed. Inlet velocity profile sensitivity confirmed negligible (< 2% RH change) justifying uniform inlet assumption."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental hemolysis data drawn from three independent laboratory replicates of the FDA pump benchmark, each with n=5 NIH measurements per operating point. Inter-laboratory variability characterized; coefficient of variation below 15% across all operating points. Sample representativeness confirmed relative to COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency between validation experiment input parameters and COU simulation inputs assessed via parameter mapping table. Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity, density) matched to within 3% of clinical blood properties at 37°C. Pump geometry equivalency confirmed via dimensional metrology report. Reynolds number similarity maintained across all 5 operating points."
    }
